    {
      "id": "tpt-title",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Thesis",
      "position": {
        "x": 400,
        "y": -500
      },
      "width": 900,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Twilite\n## The Graph is the Product\n\nTwilite is a **graph-native workspace** where visual thinking meets AI collaboration.\n\n**The core insight:** Most graph tools treat the graph as UI state. Twilite treats it as a **durable, portable artifact** — a file format that humans and AI agents can both read and write.\n\n| Capability | What It Means |\n|------------|---------------|\n| 🌐 **Web-native** | Graphs live at URLs, can be linked, embedded, shared |\n| 🤖 **AI-first** | Agents can create, update, and reason about graphs safely |\n| ⚡ **Executable** | Graphs can evolve from thinking → workflows → running code |\n\n*The editor is a means. The artifact is the thing with power.*",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
