    {
      "id": "tpt-problem",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Problem",
      "position": {
        "x": -200,
        "y": 0
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Problem\n\nVisual thinking tools are **broken**:\n\n❌ **Graphs are ephemeral** — screenshots, not files\n\n❌ **No stable identity** — can't diff, can't version, can't review\n\n❌ **AI can't help** — tools don't have machine-readable formats\n\n❌ **Build from scratch every time** — no reuse, no templates, no remix\n\n❌ **Vendor lock-in** — your thinking is trapped in someone else's app\n\n---\n\n**The deeper issue:** The graph isn't treated as the *real thing*. It's treated as a picture of the real thing.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
