    {
      "id": "tpt-alternatives",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Alternatives",
      "position": {
        "x": 1000,
        "y": 0
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Why Not Existing Tools?\n\n| Tool | Limitation |\n|------|------------|\n| **Miro/FigJam** | Graphs are visual-only, no semantic structure |\n| **Notion** | Great for docs, weak for relationships |\n| **Obsidian** | File-based but graph is read-only |\n| **React Flow** | Developer tool, not end-user product |\n| **Lucidchart** | Proprietary, no AI integration |\n| **Excalidraw** | Drawing, not structured graphs |\n\n---\n\n**Twilite's difference:**\n- Graphs are *writable* by AI (not just viewable)\n- Graphs are *portable* (not locked in)\n- Graphs can *execute* (not just visualize)",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
