    {
      "id": "tpt-progression",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Progressive Complexity",
      "position": {
        "x": -200,
        "y": 860
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Progressive Complexity\n\nNot every graph needs to execute. The platform supports a spectrum:\n\n### 1. Conceptual Graphs\n*Thinking, planning, knowledge*\n- Roadmaps, mind maps, research notes\n- Ports optional, edges are relationships\n\n### 2. Workflow Graphs\n*Typed connections, data flow*\n- Ports define inputs/outputs\n- Edges carry semantic meaning\n\n### 3. Executable Graphs\n*Scripts, plugins, live data*\n- Nodes run code (scripting API)\n- Background RPC for async operations\n- Plugin nodes extend capabilities",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
